{"id": "1466741811639750731", "channel_id": "1436913827571695898", "type": 19, "author_id": "1372028651175936080", "author_name": "Morimens", "author_bot": true, "content": "**Achieving 425 DTIDE – Full Breakdown**\n\n---\n\n### What DTIDE Is\nDTIDE = **Damage + Toughness + Initiative + Defense + Effectiveness**.  \nIt’s the overall performance metric for a character/team in Morimens.\n\n---\n\n### Core Factors to Hit 425\n\n| Factor | What to Do |\n|--------|------------|\n| **Character Level & Skills** | Max‑level your hero. Upgrade every skill/talent to its highest tier. |\n| **Equipment & Wheels** | Equip gear that boosts damage, toughness, and effectiveness. Signature wheels are usually the best choice. |\n| **Team Composition** | Build a balanced squad: mix attackers, defenders, and supporters. Synergy matters more than raw stats. |\n\n---\n\n### Step‑by‑Step Guide\n\n1. **Optimize Your Main Character**  \n   - Reach max level.  \n   - Fully upgrade all skills/talents.  \n   - Prioritize skill lines that increase damage and toughness.\n\n2. **Select the Right Gear**  \n   - Choose weapons/armor that give the highest **damage** and **toughness** rolls.  \n   - Add **effectiveness**‑focused accessories.  \n   - Use the character’s **signature wheel** for the best stat synergy.\n\n3. **Construct a Balanced Team**  \n   - **Attacker**: High damage, good initiative.  \n   - **Defender**: High toughness and defense.  \n   - **Supporter**: Boosts effectiveness for the whole squad.  \n   - Ensure each member’s abilities complement the others (e.g., a defender that can shield the attacker).\n\n4. **Fine‑Tune & Test**  \n   - Run simulations or practice battles.  \n   - Adjust gear or wheel choices if any stat feels lacking.  \n   - Keep an eye on patch notes—balance changes can shift optimal builds.\n\n---\n\n### Quick Tips\n\n- **Signature wheels** > generic wheels for most characters.  \n- **E3 copies** often give the biggest stat jumps; aim for at least E3 on key heroes.  \n- **Report bugs** if a stat isn’t calculating correctly (use <#1180845276823564288>).  \n\n---\n\n### Need a Tailored Build?\nGive me the **character** you’re focusing on and your **current team**. I’ll spit out a prec", "timestamp": "2026-01-30T10:28:18.640000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": ["694573382380945529"], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": "1466741799770001499", "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
